      "title": "Sri Lanka sells 9-year bonds at 29.52-pct, 2025 bonds offered on tap",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka has sold the entire 25 billion rupees of offered bonds maturing on 15 May 2031 at 29.52 percent, data from the state debt office showed.",
        "The debt office also sold 2,443 million rupees of 01 July 2025 bonds at 29.16 percent after offering 15 billion rupees.",
        "Dealers and the public could bid for the 2025 bond at the weighted average yield until 4.0 pm on August  31."
      ],
